Malaysia Stock Movers: Fututech, Palette, Pintaras, Systech

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-09-08T09:10:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/malaysia-stocks-fututech-palette-multimedia-uoa-development.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Malaysia trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 5 p.m. close in Kuala
Lumpur. Malaysia’s  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index rose 5.22
points, or 0.4 percent, to 1,469.83.        Fututech Bhd. (FUT)  , a lighting products supplier,
advanced 1 percent to 49 sen, its highest close since Aug. 4.
Fututech said a group led by Egovision Sdn. made a mandatory
takeover offer at 50 sen apiece for the rest of the shares it
doesn’t already own, according to a statement.        Palette Multimedia Bhd. (PMB)  , a communications and
multimedia company, slid 6.7 percent to 7 sen, its steepest drop
since Aug. 26. Palette proposed raising as much as 4.6 million
ringgit ($1.5 million) from an offering of warrants to existing
shareholders, it said in a stock exchange filing.  Pintaras Jaya Bhd. (PINT)  , a construction group, added
1.2 percent to 2.53 ringgit, the highest close since October
1997. Pintaras won a 54.9 million ringgit building contract from
Oasis Garden Development Sdn., according to a company statement.  Systech Bhd. (SYTC MK), a technology-based company,
advanced 4.6 percent to 34 sen, the highest close since Aug. 4,
after saying it plans to buy Postlink Pte, a direct-mailing
services company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chan Tien Hin in Kuala Lumpur at 
